<sentence id="5">A 29-kDa fragment , called CB23 , has now been isolated and corresponds to residues 310-486 in the EGF-like region of thrombomodulin .</sentence>
<sentence id="6">The CB23 fragment bound thrombin and accelerated thrombin-catalyzed protein C activation .</sentence>
<sentence id="7">With two separate preparations of CB23 , the Km for protein C was 1.6 and 1.9 microM and the Kd for thrombin was 8.9 and 13.2 nM .</sentence>
